{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_calhoun_ver01/data/sn83016244/00513689925/1958042301/0584.xml":{"full_text":"TH\u00ab KiY WIST CITIZEN Wednesday, April M, 1W\nPage 6\nThe Key West Citizen\nPublished Sunday Morning and Every Week Day Afternoon.\nExcept Saturday\nn artiUN editor A Publisher\n11ARGARST FORESMANZZ City Editor\ncAt RILJ7 Advertising Manager\nwftkXr \u00abO\u00abBTW u Clroulation Manaser\nPERCY CURRT Mechanical Superintendent\nMEMBER OF ASSOCIATED PRESS\nEntered at Key West. Florida as\nSecond Clans Matter\nCARRIER SUBSCRIPTION RATES\nTear\nI Months\n1 Month\n1 Week MAIL RATES\nt Tear\nMonths\nI Months 55\n1 Month r _\n(No wotkiy mail aubacrlptlona Accepted)\nNATIONAL ADVERTISING REPRESENTATIVES:\nTHEIS A SIMPSON. CO, INC.\n1 E \u00bb4th St., New fork 21. N. T.\nBranch Offices In Principal Cities\nHousewives Can Stem Recession\nIt is a matter of economic record that women now\ncontrol moat of the money in the country in investments\nand that the housewife's buying control also twists the\npurse strings.\nWith these facts in mind, a woman economist and\nhousewife, Jo Bingham, who is an executive of the Gov\nernment Finance Department of the National Associa\ntion of Manufacturers, declares that women can stop\nthe recession.\nShe advises that psychology is a large factor in\neither a recession or a boom, and warns against a pessi\nmistic attitude. Normal buying, not buying sprees, and\n.bargain hunting, as usual, will help ward off a slump.\nThe sharpest decline in purchases is in the special\nfields as buying of a new automobile, according to statis\ntics.\nHowever, Research Institute adds that personal\npanicky refusal to spend money is only one cause of\nsetbacks in the national economy. The other influences\ninclude production cuts, rising cost of foodstuffs and\nhousing; expansion slow ups and, of course, the tide.of\nunemployment.\nTwo other research psychologists come up with\nother theories. A Research Institute spokesman warns\nagainst \"saving beyond normal saving.\u201d This upsets\nthe national balance and the old hoarding routine may\nresult in a disastrous slowup of remedial economy\nmeasures.\nA psychologist, whose business it is to find out the\nmotives behind reactions of the general public, con\ntributes the idea that consumers are more irritated than\nfrightened when prices are suddenly slashed during\nrecession periods.\nThe consumer begins to believe he has been paying\ntoo much and feels that he has been cheated during\nphases of prosperity. The immediate reaction is to\nwait until costs hit rock bottom before resuming any\nbuying.\nExperts advise, in the light of this motivational re-\nsearch, that not just a reduction of costs is what would\nsolve the problem, they point out that a better com-\nmunication between the advertiser and the consumer,\nwith explanation of price policies, should be estab-\nlished.\nSumming up these theories and the given factors,\nit all boils down to the fact that the average housewife 1\ncan stem recession by keeping her courage, her head,\nher temper, and, by shopping for the most and best she\ncan get for her money, keep herself, her family and na\ntional economy on an even keel.\nI\nA university authority on language says the use of\nain\u2019t is permissible in speech but not in writing. We\nain\u2019t so sure about that.\nEven though thousands of Americans will neglect\nvoting this year, all'would fight to the last ditch any\nattempt to take away their right to vote.\nEven the men who have been hollering loudest\n-about that awful sack look have to admit it: A pretty\n\u201cgirl looks pretty, no matter what kind of a getup she\nwears. 7\nyiosswjidPuz^e\nAOBOM\nI.UMy\n4 Organa of\ni W*ot\u00aeh\nI. Rotating\nmeehantcel\nP* rU\nn Bn** Nd\nbird\n14 Oa Mm\n\u25a0MMAit\nM. Strhsgof\nears\n11. Give back\nIt. Culmination\nIt. Sin of the\nzodiac\nM. Nontiro\nRl.Pomm\n\u00bbOut\u00abt\nIt. Canvas\nshelter\nX M Guided\n\u2018MOcean\nM Aeriform\nf tuid\n\n>7. While\n2t Printed\nM. Patent\n32. Plaything\n33. Dine\nM. Oriental\ndwelling\nW. Uncanny\n17. Existence\nM. Contned\nM Attempt\n44. Worthless\nfragment\n41. Gr. letter\n41. exclama\ntion of\npraise\n44. Asiatic\npalm\n44. Princely\nItalian\nhouse\n47. Places\nrubbed out\n41. Remainder\n54 Since:\nScotch\n\u20221. Weaken\nSolution of Yesterday's Puente\nDOWN\n1. Part of a\nplay\n1. Processions\n3. Followed\n4. Cord\n5. At home\nt. According\nto delibera\ntive usage\n7. Mixed rain\n'and snow\nONE WHO NEVER SEEMS TO GO HUNGRY\ntern NwOfefsn\npv a AC r\nhwrdS If/ lIK r\nif x Y\nr I AC)\nI|J||\u00ab -7'\nBased On Simple Color Test Showing Ovulation Time\nSponsor Says New Method Is\nApproved By Catholic Church\nBy RINNIE TAYLOR II\nAP Science Reporter i\nLOS ANGELES GT A new\nbirth control method, ssid by its\nsponsor to have the approval of\nleading Catholic Church officials,\ni was described here today in a\nmedical movie.\nThe procedure does not inter-.\nfere directly with the reproductive\nprocess. It simply warns a couple\nwhen to abstain from sex relations\nif they do not want a child and\nwhen to indulge if they do want\na baby.\nIt is based on a simple coloi;\ntest which shows the woman\u2019s\novulation time the period dur- 1\ning which an egg comes into po\nsition for fertilization. But behind\nit is a graphic piece of research\nshowing how the egg escapes from\nthe ovary and how it may stay\nnear the womb until picked up\nby an ovarian tube to await fer\ntilization by the male sperm to\nstart a human life.\nThe odyssey of the egg was\nshown in a color film by Dr. j\nJoseph Bernard Doyle, of Tufts\nUniversity, Boston, before the\nAmerican College of Obstetricians\nand Gynecologists. It was the\nfilm\u2019s premiere.\nDr. Doyle, a Catholic, is direc\ntor of the fertility clinic at St.\nElizabeth's Hospital and a re\nsearch associate at St. Margaret\u2019s\nMaternity Center, both in Boston.\nDr. Doyle told reporters the new\ncolor test method has the approv\nal of Archbishop Richard J. Cush\ning of Boston; The Rev. John C.\nFord, professor of moral theology\nat Boston College; and the Rev.\nGerald Kelly of St. Mary\u2019s Col\nlege. St. Mary\u2019s, Kan.\nThe scientific facts behind the\ntest ate not new. Researchers\npreviously determined that when\negg is released from an ovary\nit is a free agent having no con\nnection with a blood vessel to ob\ntain food. It has to get its nourish\nment in its surroundings, which\nare the secretions in the area of\nthe womb.\nDr. Charles Birnberg, a Brook\nlyn researcher, found that the\nsecretions contain sugar to feed\nKey West\nIn Days Gone By\nApril 23, im\nSunday, no paper.\n\nApril 23, IMS\nExalted Ruler Frank Bentley,\ngeneral chairman of the Elks Stale\nconvention, aaid today the the pa\nrade Tuesday will begin at Du\nval and United Streets and end\nat Duval and Caroline Streets. The\nElks began arriving here today\nfor the convention.\n\nW. A. Stevens, a Florida High\nway Patrolman, drove from Mi\nami to Key West in two hours\nand nine minutes yesterday? The\nrush trip was to bring pla*ma\nhere for a new-born baby.\nMaine Lobsters Scarce\nPORTLAND, Maine UP Lob\nsters are getting scarce off\nMaine\u2019s rocky coast with a con\nsequent rise in prices. Dealers\nblame a rough winter, corriplicat\ned by spring storms and fog.\n1\n2. Domestic\nanimal\n3. Expiates\nIt. Feeble\nminded\n11. Paid out\n13. Loses\nbrightness\n,17. Thue\n31. Palm leaf\n22 Sheep-\nkilling\nparrot\n32. Urchin\n23 Pigpen\n24. Receive\n22 Kind of\nbeen\n22 Dance step\n30 Cure-all\n31 Skill\n3k Appoint\nments to\nmeet\n34. Restrains\n35 Volatile\nliquid\nM Uneven\n37. Eagles\nM So. Amor,\ncountry\n40 Ahead\n41. Foundation\n43 Aged:\nabbr.\n46. Serpent\n44 Artiste\nI\nthe egg, and that the sugar is i\nthere only when the egg is pres-\nent.\nDr. Doyle\u2019s film shows the ac. 1\ntion of a woman's reproductive\norgans. It was taken while she\nwas undergoing surgery. It shows\nthe ovarian tubes extending their p\ni ends downward to the area of the\ncervix or mouth of the womb.\nThey function like suction hoses.\nThey pick up the live egg and\nhold it until it either dies or be\ncomes fertilized by a male sperm\nmoving upward through the\nwomb, then out into the tube\nthrough the tube's connection with\nthe back portion of the womb.\nThe egg can live only 24 hours\nor so after it leaves the ovary,\nand only about 12 hours in the\ntube, Dr. Doyle said. If it dies,\nthe sugar in the secretions dis\nappears.\nTo* test for the presence of sugar\nI,\nIl 1\nCatalan Solas A S fBl wM*\n^ouuck\nsipa?s\nI I HL Hi\nI jp\nI 11 i I 11 jI. 9 U 11'1'1 9rM\nI HHI I\nw ss *\u201dT! V J s w\n\u25a0No monthly I whumidifies, I |qss V trim W\npayments A circulates A fljr A Slenderette j\nuntil June oir styling\n;i .X v'\ne,.\nONE WEEK ONLY!\n's^tuOM Mwiu\u2019 ori no Slm d\nI ATAKA PHONE CY 6-3531\n\u00abase ULHIIU\nl*\"\n\nX\na small piece of commercially\nprepared tape on a stick or tam-|\npon is held against the mouth off\nthe womb for five minutes, >then\nwithdrawn. If sugar is present, the\ntape turns green; if not, the tape\nremains a pale yellow or turns\nonly very slightly green.\nI\nCARD OF THANKS I\nWe wish to thank our kind\nfriends and relatives for the\nkindness and sympathy extend\ned us during the illness and af- I\nter the death of.our beloved\nMother, RITA MARY PEREZ.\nAlso, we thank those who sent i\nflowers. May God's grace re\ndeem their friendliness with\nhis richest rewards.\nMR. ROGELIO PEREZ\nAND FAMILY.\n'oupk Eleerion To Stop Harin' Good OHsen, Pushed Around\nCouncilwoman Says Law Comes\nFirst; Demands Resignations\nBELTON, Mo. US Mrs.'Tillie\nQuick said today she hates to take\nissue with her friends but duty\ndemands it.\nMrs. Quick, a 49 yesr-oid house\nwife, is the first woman member\nof Belton\u2019s City Council. At her\nfirst Council meeting, she de\nmanded that Mayor'William V.\nPowell, Aiderman Fred Folk, and\nJ. Maurice Robie, superintendent\nof pulflic works, resign.\nShe said the three officials bad\nbeen doing business with the city\n(pop. 1,233). In Missouri, that\u2019s\nillegal.\n\u201cI don\u2019t hsve a thing againdt\nthe mayor and the others,\" Mrs.\nQuick said today. \"They\u2019ve been\nmy friends and I would like for\nthem to remain my friends. I\nhope they will be\u2014when this is all\nover.\nCub Scout News I\nOn Saturdsy April 11, the 'hoy\nScout Merit Badge Show and Cub\nScout Advancement Display was\nheld at the Memorial Junior High\nGymnasium from I a. m. to I\np. m.\nDen No. 7 of Pack 257 put on\na skit between 8 p. m. and 7 p. m.\nThere are 12 achievements thgt\na Cub Scout must achieve before\u25a0\nhe becomes a Wolf Cub Scout\nand these are what the Cub\nScouts demonstrated in their skit.\nThey are: 1. Feats of Skill. 2.\nConducting a Flag Ceremony S.\nKeeping Well 4. Helping in the\nHome 5. Whittling 8. Collections\n7. Keeping s Scrapbook 8. Tying\nThings 9. Safety 10. Home Games\n11. Know Your Neighborhood and\n12. Reading,\nThe Cub Scouts that took part\nin the skit were: Michael Legge,\nGlenn Curry, Bill Mudd, Jose\nBerio, Robert Hamilton, Robert\nPerkins and Rick Kushman.\nMrs. Wanda. Legge is the Den\nMother.\nOn Tuesday, April 22, the re-\nIj a J\nmhmm\n\"But I just had to set v ,ew\nthings straight. It seems to me\nthat there\u2019s some skeletons which\ncoed to be dragged out of the\nBelton closet end there\u2019s no\nbetter time than the present.\nMrs. Quick said she has written\nto Missouri Atty. Gen. John M.\nDalton to find out how to get a\nstate investigation of her three\nfriends.\nMayor Powell, Aiderman Polk\nand Robie said they have no in\ntention of resigning. Powell ad\nmitted Mrs. Quick\u2019s chsrges, but\nsaid he acted in the city\u2019s interest.\nPowell, a contractor, said he\ncollected $1,889.81 for repairing\nCity Hall but only after the city\nfailed to get any bldg on the work.\nFolk, an implement dealer, was\naccused of selling machinery\nparts to the city. He has remained\ngular weekly meeting of Den 7,\nPack 257 wu held.\nThe Cub Scouts worked on a\nMother\u2019s Day project and played\ngames.\nThe Scouts attending the meetin\nwere: Michael Legge, Glenn Cur\nry, Robert Perkins, Jose Berio,\nRick *Kushmaa and Antonio Fer\nnandez.\nAfter the meeting adjourned, re\nfreshments of lemonade and cook\nies, was enjoyed, furnished by Mrs.\nR. Hamilton.\nExplorer Still\nTransmits Signals\nPASADENA, Calif. GF The\nlow.power radio of the Explorer I\nsatellite is still transmitting cos\nmic ray information back to earth\nsays Dr. Norman Jacobson of\nthe Jet Propulsion Laboratory at\nthe California Institute of Technol\nogy.\nTHE KEY WEST CITIZEN\nRadio and Television Listings\nCHANNEL 4 TV WTVJ\nW\u00bbNKBDAV nVININS\nf:U Seerts S M Bit Record*\nt:W WMther S;W Millionaire\n4:M Reale! N Get Secret\ns Hour\nT.-ae SUent Serv. ujo Weather\nT:SO 1 Love Lucy II:IS Sports\n4:00 Leave It 11:30 Star Feat.\nvat asnav vobnins\n4:3S Early Show S:H News. W'ther\n12 JU*!:. w ,h r How You Rate\nIS 5 n\u00ab\u00abroe* 10:10 A. Godfrey*\n4:X Playhouse 11:00 A. Godfrey\n11:30 Dotte*\nCHANNEL 7 TV WCKT\nWIDNISDAT BONINO\n2 S e w thel 1, 00 Your Life*\nO:4S Huntly-Br*nkly 10:30 S'n Franciieo\nGray Ghost 11:00 News\nZ 2 XM on Yrain u io Weather\n5 2 11:15 B wrt\u00ab\n0:00 Kraft Theatre 11:30 Jack Paar\nTBUSSDAI MORNING\n\u201cJ, 1 1 4:30 Today*\n7 2? J' xl y 4:05 News\n7to 2 Rom r Hoom\nT.jo Today* in oo a. Francis*\nS W Tutev* J? 2 I\"*'-\n1 a n K-2.J I ,1: Price Rtfht\n4.35 News U;W Tnlth<\nCHANNEL 10. TV WPST-TV\nWEDNESDAY EVENINS\nI S \u00a3-_* \u25a0\u2022\u2018tv White*\n10:00 Boxin.\nS\u2019S ~:S0 S^rto\nSiSf* 11:00 N\n1 11:10 Sport*\nO.W Tombatone U'O s ifl\nnUEBDAY MOBNINa\n|>\u00bb1\u00bb Theatre\nSJ?? 1 11:00 Trouble Fr.\n\u2019eS^T\"** I Moral.\nWBSDAY AFTIBNOON\nI U:M \u00dcberare im\ni I.JJT.UIT.w. ISWwS.\n2:00 Alec Cib*M m ?*\u00ae2\u00abt.nd\ni ew Aiec Gtbaea S:00 W. Woodpkr.\n0:00 Mickey Moim\nWKWF RADIO\nWEDNESDAY EVENING\nE? Moron I M Hornblower\nl^^\nits\nJ:0